{{see|groß}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''gros'', {{L.}} ''grossus''

===Adjective===
'''gross'''  ([[grosser]], [[grossest]])
# [[disgusting]], [[rude]]
# [[bulky]]
# [[coarse]]; vulgar, low, obscene, or impure
# [[dull]]
# Great; large; bulky; fat; of huge size; excessively large.
# Great; palpable; serious; vagrant; shameful; as, a gross mistake; gross injustice; gross negligence.
# the [[whole]] amount; [[entire]]; [[total]]

====Translations====
*Swedish: [[grov]] (3)

===Noun===
'''gross''' (''singular and plural'')
# [[twelve]] [[dozen]]
# the total [[earnings]] or [[amount]], before [[expenses]] or [[exception]]s are deducted (contrast [[net]])

====Translations====
*Swedish: [[#Swedish|gross]] {{n}} (1), [[brutto]] {{n}} (2)

===Verb===
#to earn money, not including expenses
#:''The movie '''gross'''ed three million on the first weekend.''

